   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">You can modify dynamic messages by inserting a field of different form through UI using <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Insert Other Form Field</uicontrol> option. You can also modify the variables in the dynamic messages using Google Blockly (Blockly).</context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the module menu, click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Administration</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ADMINISTRATION</uicontrol> page is displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the navigation pane, expand the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Configuration Toolkit</uicontrol> folder, and then click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Error Message Configurator</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ERROR MESSAGE CONFIGURATOR</uicontrol> list page is displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ERROR MESSAGE CONFIGURATOR</uicontrol> list page, select the appropriate error message, and then click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Edit</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ERROR MESSAGE CONFIGURATOR</uicontrol> page is displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Based on the error message in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Value</uicontrol> field, rewrite the error message in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">New Error Message</uicontrol> field. </cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Place the cursor where the dynamic variable must be inserted in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">New Error Message</uicontrol> field.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Insert Other Form Field</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">A pop-up is displayed where you can search and retrieve the fields from other modules or forms.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To search and retrieve the appropriate field information from other modules or forms, perform the following steps: </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li outputclass="break_avoid" class="- topic/li ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Read Data</uicontrol>.<note class="- topic/note ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Read Data</uicontrol> feature retrieves the appropriate information from other modules or forms using a reference field that is common between the source and the destination form.</note>
                     <p outputclass="break_avoid" class="- topic/p ">The following screen is displayed on the right pane of the screen. <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                           <title class="- topic/title "/>
                           <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/Read_Data.jpg"
                                  class="- topic/image "
                                  placement="inline"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">To search the appropriate information from the destination form, in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">SELECT</uicontrol> field, define the appropriate values in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Select Module</uicontrol>, <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Select Form</uicontrol>, and <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Select Field</uicontrol>.<note class="- topic/note ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">SELECT</uicontrol> field searches for the defined values in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Select Field</uicontrol> from the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Select Form</uicontrol> that belongs to the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Select Module</uicontrol> entities.</note>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">To define the relationship between the destination form and the source form, in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">WHERE</uicontrol> field, define the appropriate values in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Select Module</uicontrol>, <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Select Form</uicontrol>, and <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Select Field</uicontrol>.<note class="- topic/note ">
                        <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                           <li class="- topic/li ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">WHERE</uicontrol> field acts as the reference identifier between the source and the destination form.</li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">WHERE</uicontrol> field retrieves the defined values from the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Select Field</uicontrol> of the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Select Form</uicontrol> that belongs to the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Select Module</uicontrol> entities.</li>
                        </ul>
                     </note>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">To define the identifier of the record, click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Filters</uicontrol>, and then use the appropriate filters as applicable:<note class="- topic/note "> Once added, you can remove the filter by dragging and dropping it to <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/Delete_icon.png"
                               class="- topic/image "
                               placement="inline"/> in the center right corner of the screen.</note>
                     <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Get Value of</uicontrol>: To retrieve a list of identifiers from the source form, perform the following steps:<ol class="- topic/ol ">
                              <li outputclass="break_avoid" class="- topic/li ">Drag and drop the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Get Value of</uicontrol> filter in the double quoted empty field.<note class="- topic/note ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Get Value of</uicontrol> filter defines which identifier or reference field should be validated from the source form to retrieve a field from the destination form.</note>
                                 <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                                    <title class="- topic/title "/>
                                    <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/Read_Data_GetValue_Filter.jpg"
                                           class="- topic/image "
                                           placement="inline"/>
                                 </fig>
                              </li>
                              <li outputclass="break_avoid" class="- topic/li ">Place the cursor in the empty field adjacent to the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Get Value of</uicontrol> filter.<p class="- topic/p ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Search Fields</uicontrol> bar is displayed.<fig class="- topic/fig ">
                                       <title class="- topic/title "/>
                                       <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/Get_Value_Of_Search_Field.jpg"
                                              class="- topic/image "
                                              placement="inline"/>
                                    </fig>
                                 </p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">To add fields to the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Get Value of</uicontrol> filter, search the field name in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Search Fields</uicontrol> bar, and select the appropriate field when it is displayed.</li>
                           </ol>
                        </li>
                        <li outputclass="break_avoid" class="- topic/li ">
                           <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Resolve Value of</uicontrol>: To retrieve the common attributes between the source and the destination form, perform the following steps: <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                              <li outputclass="break_avoid" class="- topic/li ">Drag and drop the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Resolve Value of</uicontrol> filter in the double quoted empty field.<note class="- topic/note "> The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Resolve Value of</uicontrol> filter consists of <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Parent Module Id</uicontrol>, <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Module ID</uicontrol>, Project details, and user details that are used as identifiers.</note>
                                 <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                                    <title class="- topic/title "/>
                                    <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/Read_Data_Select_Resolver_Filter.jpg"
                                           class="- topic/image "
                                           placement="inline"/>
                                 </fig>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">Click the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Select Resolver</uicontrol> field adjacent to the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Resolve Value of</uicontrol> filter.<fig class="- topic/fig ">
                                    <title class="- topic/title "/>
                                    <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/Select_Resolver.jpg"
                                           class="- topic/image "
                                           placement="inline"/>
                                 </fig>
                              </li>
                              <li outputclass="break_avoid" class="- topic/li ">From the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Select Resolver</uicontrol> drop-down list, select the appropriate attributes. </li>
                           </ol>
                        </li>
                     </ul>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Save</uicontrol>. </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The selected variables are added to the appropriate place in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">New Error Message</uicontrol> field.<p class="- topic/p ">Alternatively, you can click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Restore</uicontrol> to modify the values.</p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Save</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The modified error message is displayed in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ERROR MESSAGE CONFIGURATOR</uicontrol> list page for the respective record.</info>
         </step>
      </steps>
